## Description
The**&nbsp;FTP endpoint **resource&nbsp;allows to deliver input files to an FTP server.

## Additional creation parameters
None.

## Resource editor
None.

## Deploy parameters
![](data:image/png;base64,)

Section

Field

Description

**Configuration**

**Tenant**

Select the&nbsp;**Tenant** on which you want to deploy the resource from the drop-down menu.

**Server**

**Protocol**

Select the protocol to use for the connection to the server:

- **FTP**

- **SFTP**

**Host**

Server name

**Port**

Port number for the selected&nbsp;**Protocol**

The default values are:

- **21** for FTP

- **22** for SFTP

**Path**

Remote path on the filesystem of the server where the files will be transferred

> Note

This is a relative path to the user's home folder on the FTP server, that must be provided by the Client in the setup phase.

The specified folder must already exist on the FTP server.

**Authentication**

**Username**

Username to authenticate to the server

**Password**

Password to authenticate to the server

**Private key**

Click&nbsp;**Upload** to select the private key to use for SFTP authentication.

> Note

This option is only displayed when you select the SFTP protocol.

> Tip

Click **Publish **to publish the release on the tenant.

Click **Deploy** to publish and enable the release on the tenant.
